[SN]TITLE[SN]
Car driver, 18, charged after bus hits scaffolding in Aberdeen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A teenage car driver has been charged after a collision led to a bus hitting scaffolding in Aberdeen, injuring three people.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened on Monday on Union Street beside the Summer Street junction at about 11:35.
Three people were injured but not seriously.
Police Scotland said an 18-year-old man who was driving a Volkswagen Polo involved in the incident was due at Aberdeen Sheriff Court at a later date.
